		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What about the OneStation?  I'm sure it's come and gone already, but it was a special handheld console where the cartridges are actually full systems with built-in multicarts.  They are just cartridges which get access to the power, screen, speakers, and joypad through the cartridge slot.
<br />For example, there were famiclone cartridges with 78-in-1 games or whatever number it was.  Then there were megadrive multicarts as well.

		

